289738 ehas, for at least ten years, been an Advocate.
1892925 3Subject to the provisions of sub- sections (4) and (5), the Chairman and other Members of the Tribunal shall be appointed by the President of India after consultation with the Chief Justice of India.
787799 4The Chairman and other Members shall be appointed by the President of India on the recommendation of a Selection Committee ap- pointed by the Central Government consisting of the following, namely:--
406066 aChief Justice of the High Court of Delhi or his nominee who shall be a sitting Judge of the High Court;
1950753 bChairman of the Tribunal (except in case of the appointment of the Chairman);
1827871 cSecretary to the Government of India in the Ministry dealing with Legal Affairs;.
753094 dSecretary to the Government of India in Ministry dealing with Urban Development;
1005811 eChief Secretary to the Government of the National Capital Territory of Delhi.
